      "comment": {
        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13034826/comment/15826652",
            "id": "15826652",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Just to make sure we capture part of the discussion at the end of YARN-5378:\nFor a cloud environment, clusters may be ephemeral and come and go relatively quickly. For that use-case it is desirable to enumerate clusters. I think that is still a little different than this specific jira, which would take an app ID and return the list of clusters that this app ID occurred on. Note that in the vast majority of cases this would return only 1 cluster (or none I suppose). The use-case of enumerating clusters should use useful without _any_ arguments.\nThat can happen in two ways: either strongly write this for every app, which means that we keep inserting / overwriting, or process this after the fact in the back-end. In either case, that should be a separate jira from this one imho, unless I mis-understood the discussion on YARN-5378. cc [~rohithsharma] [~varun_saxena] [~sunilg]",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-17T19:26:37.395+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-17T19:26:37.395+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13034826/comment/15826724",
            "id": "15826724",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "bq. In either case, that should be a separate jira from this one imho\nYes, I agree. That should be a separate JIRA.\nFrom an implementation point of view as well, we will have to see how to do it. And where to maintain this info. Have a separate table? If yes, when to update it? On every publish of an entity (will be too much) or on a certain event say, application created event or something else. \nOr we can even follow YARN-5739 kind of approach to list the clusters from app table.\nEither way, it will require more discussion and should not block this JIRA for which we are clear regarding what needs to be done. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2017-01-17T20:06:43.077+0000",
            "updated": "2017-01-17T20:06:43.077+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13034826/comment/15826725",
            "id": "15826725",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "body": "bq. In either case, that should be a separate jira from this one imho,\nExactly!! These are 2 separate REST endpoints. \n* Give an appId, return list of clusterId's. \n*  */clusterids* returns list of clusterIds. I was giving use case for the necessity of new REST API */clusterids* that return list of clusterId's from back-end. I will create new JIRA for this discussion. \n\nMay be REST API could be in */clusterids* and */clusterids/$appId* for both new endpoints. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
